      "side": 1,
      "message": "If we are not tracking the consumed messages in this path, does it make sense to track the failed-to-ack messages as well or not?",
      "revId": "11cf83922b3185071fbc134e16a826f1808e4316",
      "serverId": "d5d70762-12d0-45a1-890d-524b12d3f735"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "9434dfa6_ab8b3066",
        "filename": "src/main/java/com/gerritforge/gerrit/plugins/multisite/consumer/AbstractSubcriber.java",
        "patchSetId": 15
      },
      "lineNbr": 81,
      "author": {
        "id": 1015244
      },
      "writtenOn": "2026-05-08T15:18:31Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I think it still makes sense to track ack failures on this path.\n\nEven if we don\u0027t count these events as \"consumed\", we are still trying to acknowledge them to the broker after deciding to drop them locally.\n\nBut if acking one of them fails, I’d still like the failed-ack metric to move.\n\nWDYT?",
      "parentUuid": "4004ff75_f144c09b",
      "revId": "11cf83922b3185071fbc134e16a826f1808e4316",
      "serverId": "d5d70762-12d0-45a1-890d-524b12d3f735"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "ef9a8baa_4cad6da1",
